                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " For correction  of",
                "fusion residues cross sections formed directly in their",
                "ground states by particle decay."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors-.The gamma-ray technique is used with a new",
                "absolute normalization method which is independent of",
                "charge collection, allowing one to monitor at the same",
                "time the carbon buildup as the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "date": 20060706,
                "history": "C"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " By S.B"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "date": 20070605,
                "history": "U"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Last checking has been done."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "An amorphous carbon foil deposited onto a thick Ta-",
                "backing so that the evaporation residues were fully",
                "stopped.",
                "To prevent too much target thickening, three carbon",
                "foils were used in successive stages of the experiment",
                "with repeat points taken whenever the target changed.",
                "The original foil thicknesses were 19.2+-0.9-mug/cm**2,",
                " 22.7+-1.0-mug/cm**2 and 29.9+-1.4-mug/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Barrier penetration model calculations.",
                "The extrapolation of the astrophysical S-factor to",
                "lower energies is discussed on the basis of the unified",
                "data."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "6-C-12(6-C-12,EL)6-C-12,,DA",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "6-C-12(6-C-12,EL)6-C-12,,DA",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "6-C-12(6-C-12,EL)6-C-12",
                        "target": "6-C-12",
                        "projectile": "6-C-12",
                        "process": "EL",
                        "product": "6-C-12",
                        "quantity": ",DA",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",DA"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A silicon surface barrier",
                "detector was placed at 160-degree in order to measure",
                "the C-12 ions elastically scattered from the",
                "Ta-backing.",
                "This produces a thick-target spectrum that can be used",
                "to determine the absolute normalization factors",
                "involving both the target thickness and the integrated",
                "number of projectiles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two detectors placed at 125- and 55-degrees were",
                "used to measure the secondary gamma-rays emitted by",
                "the evaporation residues.  Measurements at these angles",
                "effectively minimize the effects of possible",
                "anisotropies in the gamma-radiation and the comparison",
                "of spectra at the two angles permits easy",
                "identification of any doppler shift effects."
              ]
            }
          ],
